        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 18 at 3:25PM EDT by NWS Raleigh NC</headline>
        <description>At 325 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
RDU International, or near Raleigh, moving east at 20 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Raleigh, Wake Forest, Zebulon, Bunn, Knightdale, Wendell, Rolesville,
Youngsville, Pilot, and William B Umstead State Park.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
